name: Dooney & Bourke All-Weather Leather bag
description:
Dooney & Bourke started in 1975 when Peter Dooney and Frederic Bourke launched their namesake in South Norwalk, Connecticut. The duo started off with two introductory products: belts, which were popular due to their unique vibrant colors and stripes, and classic suspenders.

In 1981, Dooney & Bourke branched out into the handbag business with the release of the Tack Case and the Equestrian Bag, both made from bridle leather.  In 1983, with the development of their famous All-Weather Leather (AWL) bag, the first AWL handbag collection was released featuring a duck logo with a russet leather trim.

The Pendleton Board Shirt (button up) was a huge fashion staple throughout the Southern California 1960’s surf craze. So much in fact the Beach Boys Original name was the Pendletones!

name: Schott Bomber SOLD OUT
description:
Schott was founded in 1913 by brothers, Irving and Jack Schott. In
1928, they were also the first company to make a jacket specifically
for motorcycle riding. It was named “The Perfecto” and was made
popular by many stars like The Ramones, Peter Fonda and Marlon Brando
among notable others. The company is also known for manufacturing the
US Navy’s pea coat during WWII. You can still find these coats today
at many high-end retailers all across the world.

name: Burberrry by: Gitman bros SOLD OUT
description:
Burberry was founded by 21-year-old Thomas Burberry, 157 years ago.. A company rich in functional innovations as well responsible for high fashion trends...

In 1914 Burberry was commissioned by the War Office to adapt its officer's coat to suit the conditions of contemporary warfare, resulting in the "trench coat". After the war, the trench coat became popular with civilians. The iconic Burberry check pattern was created in the 1920s and used as a lining in its trench coats. 

Today their USA Made shirts are produced by the American heritage manufacturer, Gitman Brothers.
